◆ Average() [5/40]

static IProducer<float> Microsoft.Psi.Operators.Average ( this IProducer< float >  source,
DeliveryPolicy  deliveryPolicy = null 
)
static

Compute the average of a stream of float values.

Parameters
sourceThe source stream.
deliveryPolicyAn optional delivery policy.
Returns
Stream of average values.

This operator considers the average of a sequence of values containing NaN to be NaN. Consequently, once a value of NaN is encountered on the source stream, the corresponding output value and all subsequent output values will be NaN.

)

Interpolate a stream using a specified interpolator at a given sampling interval.

Template Parameters
TType of source messages.
TInterpolationType of the interpolation result.
Parameters
sourceSource stream.
samplingIntervalInterval at which to apply the interpolator.
interpolatorInterpolator to use for generating results.
alignmentDateTimeIf non-null, this parameter specifies a time to align the sampling messages with. If the paramater is non-null, the messages will have originating times that align with (i.e., are an integral number of intervals away from) the specified alignment time.
deliveryPolicyAn optional delivery policy.
Returns
Output stream.

◆ Max() [1/32]

static IProducer<double> Microsoft.Psi.Operators.Max ( this IProducer< double >  source,
DeliveryPolicy  deliveryPolicy = null 
)
static

Compute the maximum of a stream of double values.

Parameters
sourceThe source stream.
deliveryPolicyAn optional delivery policy.
Returns
Stream of maximum values.

This operator considers the maximum of a number and NaN to be NaN. Consequently, once a value of NaN is encountered on the source stream, the corresponding output value and all subsequent output values will be NaN.

static IProducer<double> Microsoft.Psi.Operators.Min ( this IProducer< double >  source,
DeliveryPolicy  deliveryPolicy = null 
)
static

Compute the minimum of a stream of double values.

Parameters
sourceThe source stream.
deliveryPolicyAn optional delivery policy.
Returns
Stream of minimum values.

This operator considers the minimum of a number and NaN to be NaN. Consequently, once a value of NaN is encountered on the source stream, the corresponding output value and all subsequent output values will be NaN.

◆ NullableSelect< TIn, TOut >() [1/2]

Func< TIn, Envelope, TOut >  selector,
DeliveryPolicy  deliveryPolicy = null 
)
static

Executes a transform function for each non-null item in the input stream, generating a new stream with the values returned by the function, or null if the input was null. The function has access to the envelope of the input message.

Template Parameters
TInThe input message type.
TOutThe output message type.
Parameters
sourceThe source stream to subscribe to.
selectorThe function to perform on every message in the source stream. The function takes two parameters, the input message and its envelope.
deliveryPolicyAn optional delivery policy.
Returns
A stream of type TOut .

TOut :struct

◆ Sample< T >() [1/2]

static IProducer<T> Microsoft.Psi.Operators.Sample< T > ( this IProducer< T >  source,
TimeSpan  samplingInterval,
TimeSpan  tolerance,
DateTime?  alignmentDateTime = null,
DeliveryPolicy  deliveryPolicy = null 
)
static

Sample a stream at a given sampling interval, by selecting the nearest message within a given tolerance to the interpolation point.

Template Parameters
TType of source (and output) messages.
Parameters
sourceSource stream.
samplingIntervalInterval at which to apply the interpolator.
toleranceThe tolerance within which to search for the nearest message.
alignmentDateTimeIf non-null, this parameter specifies a time to align the sampling messages with. If the paramater is non-null, the messages will have originating times that align with (i.e., are an integral number of intervals away from) the specified alignment time.
deliveryPolicyAn optional delivery policy.
Returns
Sampled stream.

This operator considers the sum of a number and NaN as NaN. Consequently, once a value of NaN is encountered on the source stream, the corresponding output value and all subsequent output values will be NaN.
